data.text:
Brazen Kamala Harris sparks Donald Trump's fury after STEALING one of his flagship election policies

Harris unveiled the policy at a Las Vegas rally Saturday night - but Trump quickly accused her of stealing the idea. Harris has enjoyed a strong start to her presidential campaign, despite consistent poor poll numbers during her stint as vice president.

Woke female judge is SUSPENDED after she accused prosecutor of going after black men, changed jury's verdict and convicted defendant of non-existent crime

The Louisiana Supreme Court voted to remove 19th Judicial District Judge Eboni Johnson Rose from her elected post on an interim basis amid a formal investigation.

Horror unfolded moments after girl, 3, walked into meadow with this MUSTANG

A chilling video shows three-year-old Olivia Wilkey admiring and pointing at a horse a few feet away from her in a Nevada meadow (pictured main) just moments before it attacked her. Her mother, Haley, later told Fox 5 Vegas that she stopped recording when her son approached, and she had to scold him to slow down. In that brief moment she was looking away, Haley said the horse closed in on Olivia (inset) and kicked her in the head - leaving the young girl unresponsive.

SAUCY SECRETS: My husband dropped a fantasy on me I never saw coming - and it could ruin our whole relationship. Do I go ahead anyway?

Jana Hocking shares her best Saucy Secrets - and trademark sassy advice.

Putin orders more than 76,000 to evacuate as Ukraine launches surprise cross-border offensive into Russia

Temporary accommodation shelters have been set up across eight regions to house evacuees as the war appears to move closer to Russia

Sturgis cops reveal number of arrests made at hedonistic annual motorcycle rally... as 500,000 bikers and scantily-clad revelers pack-up to head home

Over half a million bikers and partygoers descended on Sturgis, South Dakota this week for the annual Sturgis Motorcycle Rally, where a staggering number of attendees were arrested. Arrests and citations increased this year as scantily-clad revelers filled the streets of Sturgis, surpassing numbers seen in 2023 over the week-long event. The event is known for bringing a hedonistic atmosphere to the normally sleepy Black Hills area, with UFC star Connor McGregor among those spotted among the partygoers.

EXCLUSIVENancy Grace reveals new evidence in teacher's shocking 'suicide' case that may have damaged Josh Shapiro VP chances

The case was catapulted even further into the spotlight when former Pennsylvania Attorney General Josh Shapiro emerged as a potential running mate for Kamala Harris.

Former sex worker reveals the WILDEST fantasies clients ever requested that their wives refused to perform

A woman who quit her graduate program to 'devote herself to men' has revealed what she learned about relationships - and herself - in the course of more than ten years as a sex worker.

RACE FOR THE WHITE HOUSE

Celine Dion's hilarious insult for Trump after discovering he's been playing her Titanic ballad My Heart Will Go On at his campaign rallies without permission

A classic Celine Dion song was played at Trump's campaign rally in Bozeman, Montana, shortly before he took the stage on Friday. The singer's management company has now posted a fiery response on Twitter.

Moment Donald Trump hurls vile insults at US senator over the size of his BELLY... after 'repeatedly branding Kamala a "b***h"'

Trump drew a large crowd to Bozeman, Montana on Friday night, where he focused his remarks on Democrat Senator Jon Tester - and launched several crude attacks on his weight.

Trump campaign is 'HACKED' amid claims secret documents about JD Vance's 'vulnerabilities' and court cases have been leaked

The campaign blamed 'foreign sources hostile to the United States' and cited a report on Friday that Iranian hackers attempted to hack a high-ranking official.

Kamala's VP pick Tim Walz is mocked for bizarre behavior onstage at Las Vegas rally

Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate 'Coach' Tim Walz was seen joyously clapping as he walked onstage from the podium at their Las Vegas rally on Saturday night. But while his energy and gusto was praised by attendees, many online right-wingers questioned his 'bizarre' behavior. The Las Vegas stop was the last public event of a five-city introduction of the Harris-Walz ticket.

Team Kamala is forced into admit VP pick Tim Walz LIED about fighting in a war

The Kamala Harris campaign has been forced to admit Vice Presidential candidate Tim Walz lied about fighting in a war.

Kamala Harris prepares to unveil sharp U-turns to her previously woke views on immigration and crime

As her campaign ramps up, insiders and experts have noted a significantly changing approach from Kamala Harris over the issues of crime and illegal immigration, sometimes clashing with her past.

Secrets of how Mossad kills its enemies - from paralyzing injections and electrocution to poison toothpaste and AI machine guns

Hamas's leaders are 'walking dead', promised Israel's defence minister Yoav Gallant after the October 7 atrocities: 'They are living on borrowed time.' The Israelis are making good on their word. Eleven days ago, the lethal efficiency of Israel's targeted assassinations was once more demonstrated to the world when the political head of Hamas, Ismail Haniyeh, was blown up in a guesthouse in Tehran. The Israelis have not claimed responsibility, and nor have they denied it. But everyone knows it was them. It was an extraordinary coup: the killing of one of Israel's foremost adversaries in the very heart of enemy territory. And this is the real kicker - it was on the day of the new Iranian president's inauguration. A tactical triumph for Israel. Rank humiliation for Iran.

Doctor, 43, reveals how Apple Watch saved her life by alerting her to terrifying health crisis

Erica Harris, 43, was stuck in traffic in November 2021 when she got an alert on her watch that her heart was beating too fast and irregularly.

Ritzy California coastal town at war as multimillionaire homeowners erect 'fake' private property signs to keep visitors off gorgeous secluded beach

Wealthy California homeowners appear to be putting up 'fake' private property signs on public beaches near their homes to keep crowds away and maintain their secluded, relaxing lifestyle.

Bargain hunter's delight at discovering a $9.99 'Hermes Birkin' at thrift store...but she got a nasty shock after buying it

Ashlee, a popular Canadian thrifter who goes by @msfili on TikTok, found a Hermes Birkin at her local thrift store for $9.99 last month. But while Ashlee was overjoyed with her latest find, TikTokers began expressing doubts about the authenticity of the 'pure leather' bag. The Herms Epsom Birkin 35 made with orange d'H epsom leather and palladium-Plated Hardware costs $11,500 on TheRealReal

Georgia father is arrested over horrific video of him 'abusing' sobbing toddler, 3, in Kroger parking lot

James Collins, 44, (right)has been arrested after he was filmed allegedly beating a sobbing three year old in a Kroger parking lot on August 7 (left). Footage posted online shows the suspect repeatedly yelling at a three-year-old boy inside his white GMC truck to 'shut up' and 'get in the damn car' as the toddler could be heard crying. He then slaps the boy at least three times, as he yells, 'I said shut up.'

America's most luxurious cities are revealed - but three of the top five are also a byword for grime and squalor

A new study by Dominion, an asset protection company has revealed the most luxurious American cities to live in for those seeking to indulge in finer things and enjoy opulence in life.

'We're over the moon': Gypsy Rose Blanchard reveals sex of her baby alongside boyfriend Ken Urker... eight months after her prison release

Gypsy Rose Blanchard and her boyfriend Ken Urker revealed the sex of their baby. The couple took to her Instagram on Saturday to share a video of an adorable reveal party.

Top food critic reveals the incredibly simple way of telling whether a restaurant is good

Tom Sietsema, who won an award for his series '10 Best Food Cities in America' in 2015 by the James Beard Foundation has revealed the most efficient way to recognize a delectable dining spot. In his latest article, the seasoned diner revealed his failsafe ways of vetting restaurants before requesting a table - with one that can be used without even reaching the front door.

SHOPPING: A 100 per cent natural intensive moisturising balm that costs just 9 has amassed over 2,400 five-star reviews from users wowed by its 'amazing results' on dry and sensitive skin.

EXCLUSIVEDrunk American Airlines passenger who mocked cop's penis size, wet herself and shrieked 'I am an executive platinum person' learns her fate

Angela Nicole Killian, 44, a divorced mother-of-two, was flying on American Airlines from Dallas-Fort Worth Airport to Bogota, Colombia, on September 12 last year. Newly released police bodycam video showed cops arrest her for public intoxication after staff accused her of hitting them with her phone in a rage. She claimed to have only had two 'very full' vodka tonics to drink at the airport bar, but was slurring and incoherent as she berated police, then wet herself on the floor. Killian was charged with resisting arrest and hauled before Tarrant County Criminal Court.

Why being hardworking isn't always enough to climb the career ladder - and the cringeworthy step experts say you must take to get ahead

Being a hard worker is not always enough to climb the career ladder, experts told the Wall Street Journal - instead recommending a cringeworthy step to get ahead.

Cause of death for woman, 57, who was found entangled in a baggage conveyor belt at Chicago airport revealed - as case takes shocking turn

Christine Vinton, 57, of Waxhaw Virginia, was found dead at Chicago O'Hare airport shortly before 8am on Thursday.

Invasion of enormous wild beasts leaves shocked residents in idyllic mountain towns fearing for their lives: 'I do a lot of praying'

Places including towns, farms and ranches across the Northern Rockies where they hadn't been seen in over a century are now reporting sightings. Biologists say they believe the population has now climbed to at least 2,000 and the animals are now regularly roaming outside Glacier and Yellowstone National Park.

LeBron James finds himself on the wrong end of WILD dunk from France's Guerschon Yabusele in Olympics gold medal game

LeBron James haters have a new favorite basketball player: Team France power forward Guerschon Yabusele. The former Boston Celtics prospect dropped a massive one-handed dunk on James.

Nightmare decision! Notorious 'slasher' film A Nightmare On Elm Street has 18 rating cut to 15 - as Downton Abbey creator quips showing it to teenagers is 'child abuse'

The British Board of Film Classification says the age limit to watch the 1984 horror movie, in which knife-wielding Freddie Krueger attacks teenagers as they sleep, should be lowered from 18 to 15.

'I like it way better': Britney Spears appears to SHADE Blake Lively over iconic Versace dress

Britney Spears appeared to shade Blake Lively and the 2002 Versace dress that was once Britney's worn by the Gossip Girl star at the premiere of It Ends With Us. The Toxic singer, 41, posted a video clip of herself in the short pink and blue bedazzled dress with side cutouts set to the tune of The Outfield's 1986 hit Your Love. 'UPDATED VERSION OF MY 2002 VERSACE DRESS. I like it way better. Shows my legs !!,' Spears captioned the post adding a string of emojis.

Putin on the defensive: Ukraine takes control of gas plant and Russian town as shelling continues through the night as surprise offensive that caught Moscow by surprise gathers speed

Ukrainian soldiers claiming to be from the 61st Brigade were filmed standing outside a local Gazprom facility in the town of Sudzha which is about 10 kilometers from the Ukraine border.

See the shocking moment that saw footy star accused of biting a VERY sensitive part of rival's body

St George Illawarra risk losing key players as they push towards the NRL finals after Kyle Flanagan was accused of biting Stephen Crichton in a 28-10 loss to Canterbury.

PARIS OLYMPICS 2024

Jordan Chiles is set to LOSE Olympic bronze medal after bombshell ruling against USA star

Jordan Chiles is set to lose the Olympic bronze medal she won in the women's floor final after a bombshell ruling from the Court of Arbitration of Sport on Saturday. CAS ruled the judging panel were wrong to allow an inquiry that increased Chiles' score and moved her up into bronze medal position from fifth place at the expense of Ana Barbosu, who was left in tears. USA gymnastics says it is 'devastated' by the decision.

I can't believe I'm free but you, my beloved, live in endless fear: Rescued hostage Noa Argamani's heartbreaking letter to her missing boyfriend

Noa's boyfriend Avinatan Or has not been seen since haunting footage showed him watching on helplessly, surrounded by gunmen, as Hamas militants took Noa to Gaza on a motorbike.

As Sussexes prepare for latest 'quasi royal' tour... are Harry and Meghan being used as political pawns by Colombia?

The Sussexes will begin their tour of the South American country on Thursday and will visit the capital, Bogota, the historical colonial city of Cartagena on the Caribbean coast.

Olympics drama after Team USA high-jumper Shelby McEwen refused to share his gold medal with competitor - before being dealt 'instant karma'

American high jumper Shelby McEwen split fans on Saturday when he opted against splitting gold with New Zealand's Hamish Kerr at the 2024 Olympics in Paris. 'Couldn't understand his decision and in the end it costed (sic) him the gold,' wrote on fan after McEwen fell to Kerr in a jump off. Others agreed with McEwen's ultimately doomed decision to go into a jump off to decide first and second place. 'He wanted to be Olympic champion, not joint Olympic champion,' one fan added. 'I respect it.'

New Zealand high jumper Hamish Kerr goes viral after bailing out last minute and jumping UNDER the bar - before leaping to Olympic gold just minutes later

The New Zealand athlete inexplicably acted like he'd never taken part in the discipline before and pulled out of his jump, opting to leap under the bar and land on the comfortable blue mat.

Simone Biles breaks her silence after ruling against Jordan Chiles ruling that saw USA star lose Paris Olympics bronze

Simone Biles is voicing her support for teammate Jordan Chiles amid the ongoing dispute over the Team USA star's bronze medal in the floor exercise.

Heart-wrenching moment veteran, 90, resorts to pawning jewelry to take care of his dementia-stricken wife - before stunning act of kindness changes his life

Air Force Veteran, Donald, had visited a US Gold and Pawn in Manchester, New Hampshire, to sell jewelry to help pay his bills and take care of his wife when he got the surprise of his life from store worker Jenelle Marie. 'This is the best birthday present anyone has every had!' he exclaimed. Donald will turn 91 on August 25.

Sharon Stone, 66, seen on rare outing with sons Roan, 24, and Laird, 19, as they grab lunch at Beverly Hills hotspot

Sharon Stone is in the middle of shooting the new action-thriller film Nobody 2, which serves as the direct sequel to Nobody (2021), starring Bob Odenkirk.

Woman who ballooned to 825 pounds after witnessing boyfriend's horrific murder is now deemed a 'FIRE HAZARD' with tragic result

Juaunia Bates, 33, of Wayne, Michigan, claims she's been told she's a fire hazard after it took 15 paramedics and firefighters to get her out of her apartment building after she called 911.

Katie Holmes' look-alike daughter Suri Cruise, 18, enjoys NYC outing as she prepares to head off to college

Suri Cruise was spotted enjoying the sunshine in New York City on Saturday afternoon - as she prepares to head off to college in the fall. The daughter of Katie Holmes and Tom Cruise, 18, is reportedly just one week away from moving to the dorms at Carnegie Mellon University in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. On Saturday, Suri looked relaxed as she made her way down the sidewalk with a black tote bag over one shoulder.
